  "source_id": "severe-childhood-obesity",
  "name": "Severe Childhood Obesity - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + BMI)",
  "description": "Simulates a pediatrician identifying their complete severe pediatric obesity patient population. Combines: pediatric obesity diagnosis codes and elevated BMI measurements. **First pediatric phenotype** in suite — tests age-restricted population.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete severe pediatric obesity patient population for a quality improvement initiative on lifestyle counseling and weight management. From clinical experience, severe childhood obesity patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal obesity diagnosis (parent obesity, morbid obesity, obese class II, or BMI≥40 severely obese), and most have elevated BMI measurements (≥30 kg/m², roughly the 99th percentile for adolescents).\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any severe obesity diagnosis\n2. Patients with elevated BMI (≥30 kg/m²)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found. Note: this is a pediatric population (ages 5-17).",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of obesity dx + elevated BMI. Tests Condition + Observation cross-resource union for pediatric phenotype.",
    "expected_queries": [
      "Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|414916001,http://snomed.info/sct|238136002,http://snomed.info/sct|443381000124105,http://snomed.info/sct|414915002,http://snomed.info/sct|408512008&patient.birthdate=gt2008-04-28&patient.birthdate=le2021-04-28",
      "Observation?code=http://loinc.org|39156-5&value-quantity=ge30||kg/m2&patient.birthdate=gt2008-04-28&patient.birthdate=le2021-04-28"
    ],
    "patient_filters": {
